k/level-5" title="List of HSK 5 characters" style="white-space: nowrap;">more hsk 5 charaters &raquo;</a></small></p><p><b>Frequency rank:</b> 906</p><p><b><a href="/character-list/general-standard" title="Table of General Standard Chinese Characters">General standard</a> index number:</b> 1288</p><p><b>Traditional variant:</b> <a href="/character/詩">詩</a></p><p><b>Examples of words containing this character:</b> <a href="/dictionary/卑诗" title="Bei1 Shi1">卑诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/反诗" title="fan3 shi1">反诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/古诗" title="gu3 shi1">古诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/史诗" title="shi3 shi1">史诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/吟诗" title="yin2 shi1">吟诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/唐诗" title="Tang2 shi1">唐诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/律诗" title="lu:4 shi1">律诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/情诗" title="qing2 shi1">情诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/圣诗" title="sheng4 shi1">圣诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/旧诗" title="jiu4 shi1">旧诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/艳诗" title="yan4 shi1">艳诗</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗人" title="shi1 ren2">诗人</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗仙" title="shi1 xian1">诗仙</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗句" title="shi1 ju4">诗句</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗坛" title="shi1 tan2">诗坛</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗意" title="shi1 yi4">诗意</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗文" title="shi1 wen2">诗文</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗曰" title="shi1 yue1">诗曰</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗书" title="Shi1 Shu1">诗书</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗歌" title="shi1 ge1">诗歌</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗画" title="shi1 hua4">诗画</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗礼" title="Shi1 Li3">诗礼</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗稿" title="shi1 gao3">诗稿</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗篇" title="shi1 pian1">诗篇</a>, <a href="/dictionary/诗经" title="Shi1 jing1">诗经</a></p></div><h2>English translation (based on CEDICT):</h2><div class=ceent><div style="background:#dddddd;float:both;font-family: monospace;">詩|诗[<span style="color:#990000;">Shī</span>]:</div> <div style="float:left;padding-left:15px;">- abbr. for Shijing <a href="/dictionary/詩經">詩經</a>|<a href="/dictionary